help.ban: Bans members permanently from the server.
help.config: This is a command to configure the bot's settings for the server.²Defines the role that a user will have when he arrives on the server or reset the configured role.²Sets the bot language for the server.²Changes the bot prefix for the server or reset the configured bot's prefix.²Defines the channel where the welcome/departure messages are sent.²Adds or removes a word from the list of forbidden words or reset the entire list of forbidden words.
help.createChannel: Creates a channel according to the specified type, name and category.
help.getBotIp: Sends the ip of the bot in private message.
help.github: Lists all GitHub repositories or give information about a GitHub repository of a GitHub user/organization.
help.guildInfo: Gives the nitro level, the owner of the server, the number of people not connected and connected on the server.
help.invite: Creates a server invitation or give the bot's invitation link.
help.issue: Sends an issue to our GitHub repository.
help.kick: Excludes a member from the server.
help.maths: This is a command with many uses related to mathematics.²Calculates the specified mathematical expression.²Calculates the specified mathematical expression.²Checks if a number is prime or make a list of all prime numbers up to the specified number.²Checks if a number is perfect or make a list of all perfect numbers up to the specified number.²Converts one unit of measurement to another.
help.mcServer: Gives the version, the number of connected players and the port of the specified server.
help.mute: Permanently mutes a member, unmutes if the person is already muted.
help.purge: Deletes messages by a given number between 1 and 100 (these numbers included).
help.say: Sends the specified message and includes your name if you do not have permissions to manage messages.
help.snippet: Transforms the specified code into an image.
help.spigot: Gives the name, link, ID and description of a Spigot plugin by searching for it by its ID or by its name, or search for a Spigot user.²Gives the name, link, id and description of a Spigot plugin by searching by its ID.²Gives the name, link, id and description of a Spigot plugin by searching by its name.²Find a Spigot user.
help.suggestion: Sends a suggestion to the developers.
help.tempban: Bans temporarily according to the specified time a member with his ID/mention.
help.test: A test order according to the tests to be done.
help.translate: Translates the specified sentence according to the language of the text and the language you want the text to be translated from.
help.unban: Unbans a banned member from the server.
information.unshorturl:
The argument is:

- **URL** gives the redirection of the specified url.
help.userInfo: Gives the username, the date of creation of the account, the date of when it joined the server, its activity and its nickname if it has one of the member/user with its username and its mention. If you don't put any arguments, the bot will give you your information.
information.github:
The arguments are:

- **search** search for a GitHub repository;
- **list** list of GitHub repositories.

These arguments have a sub-argument:

- **GitHub user** search for a GitHub repository in the GitHub user's GitHub repositories or list all GitHub repositories of the GitHub user.

The "**search**" argument has one more sub-argument:

- **organization GitHub** searches for a GitHub repository in a GitHub organization.

The "**search**" argument as well as the "**GitHub user**" and "**GitHub organization**" sub-arguments have one more sub-argument:

- **GitHub repository name** searches for a particular GitHub repository with its name in the repositories of a GitHub user or a GitHub organization.
information.channelMember:
The available arguments are:
- **join** will define the channel where the welcome announcements will appear.
- **leave** will define the channel where the departure announcements will appear.

After these arguments, the available arguments are **channel ID/mention**, **reset** and **this**:
- **channel ID/mention** will define the channel by its ID or mention.
- **reset** will reset the channel that has been configured.
- **this** will define the channel where the order was made.
information.config:
The available arguments are:

- **channelmember**:
This argument has sub-arguments:
- **join** concerns the welcome messages;
- **leave** concerns the departure messages.
These sub-arguments have sub-arguments:
- **reset** resets the configured room, the welcome/departure messages will be sent in the default room;
- **this** defines the salon where this order was sent;
- **identifiant/mention du salon** defines the salon according to its identifier or mention.

- **prohibitword**:
This argument has sub-arguments:
- **add** adds a word to the list of forbidden words;
- **remove** remove a word from the list of forbidden words;
- **reset** resets the entire list of forbidden words.
The **add** and **remove** sub-arguments have a sub-argument:
- **mot** is the word that will be added or removed from the list of forbidden words.

- **localization**:
This argument has sub-arguments:
- **en** sets the server bot language to English;
- **fr** sets the server bot language to French.

- **joinrole**:
This argument has sub-arguments:
- **reset** resets the configured role;
- **identifiant/mention du rôle** defines the salon according to its identifier or mention.

- **setprefix**:
This argument has sub-arguments:
- **reset** resets the configured prefix, the prefix used will be `sb!`;
- **prefix** defines the specified prefix.
information.createChannel:
The arguments are:

- **text** creates a text channel;
- **voice** creates a voice channel.

These arguments have a sub-argument:

- **name** defines the name not exceeding 100 characters of the channel.

This sub-argument has a sub-argument:

- **category's ID** defines where the channel will be created (This argument is not obligatory).
information.issue:
The argument is:

- **<--body>** defines the problem after this argument.

This sub-argument has a sub-argument:

- **problem** defines the problem.

This sub-argument has a sub-argument:

- **title** defines the title of the problem after this sub-argument (This sub-argument is not obligatory).

This sub-argument has a sub-argument:

- **problem's title** defines the title of the problem (This sub-argument is not obligatory).
information.joinRole:
The available arguments are:
- **channel ID/mention** will define the role thanks to its ID or its mention.
- **reset** will reset the role that has been configured.
information.localization:
The available languages are:
:flag_us: /:flag_gb: en
:flag_fr: fr
If the language is not configured, it will default to English.
information.maths:
The arguments are:

- **mathematical expression** OR **calculate mathematical expression** calculates the specified mathematical expression.

- **primenumber**:
This argument has sub-arguments:
- **number** verifies if the specified integer number is prime or not;
- **list** gives a list of all prime numbers starting from the specified integer number.
These sub-arguments have sub-arguments:
- **number** defines the integer number that will be used.

- **perfectnumber**:
This argument has sub-arguments:
- **number** verifies if the specified integer number is perfect or not;
- **list** gives a list of all perfect numbers starting from the specified integer number.
These sub-arguments have sub-arguments:
- **number** defines the integer number that will be used.

- **convert**:
This argument has a sub-argument:
- **number** defines the number of the first specified unit of measure to after be converted to the second specified unit of measure.
This sub-argument has a sub-argument:
- **unit of measure** defines the first specified unit of measure.
This sub-argument has a sub-argument:
- **unit of measure** defines the second specified unit of measure.
The two units of measure can be chosen from these avaible units of measure, you can't convert one unit of measure to another if they do not have the same type of measure:
information.prohibit:
The available arguments are **add**, **rem** and **reset**.
- **add** will add a word to the list of forbidden words.
- **rem** will remove a word from the list of prohibited words.
- **reset** will reset the entire list of forbidden words.
After the arguments **add** and **rem**, you must put the argument **word** which will correspond to the word that will be added or removed.
information.purge: The argument is: **number of messages** defines the number of messages that will be deleted which must be between 1 and 100 (these numbers included).
information.mcServer:
The argument is:

- **IP address of a Minecraft server** gives the server name, the server IP address, the server port, the versions accepted by the server and the number of players connected to the server.
information.say:
The argument is:

- **text** is the text the bot will say when mentioning your username if you don't have permission to manage messages.
information.snippet:
The argument is:

- program** sends an image of the specified piece of code.
information.suggestion:
The argument is:

- **suggestion** sends a suggestion to the bot's development server;
